The numbers are placed on the integer lattice in the usual “Ulam” spiral  

```
… 5 4 3 …
… 6 1 2 …
… 7 8 9 …
```

With 1 at \((0,0)\), the point \((x,y)\) lies on the layer  

\[
k=\max(|x|,|y|).
\]

For a layer \(k\;(k\ge 1)\)

* the greatest number in the layer is  

\[
M_k=(2k+1)^2
\]

and it sits at \((k,-k)\).

* The right side of the layer runs from \((k,-k+1)\) up to \((k,k)\); its first number is  

\[
S_k= (2k-1)^2+1 .
\]

For a point on the right side \((k,y)\)

\[
\text{value}=S_k+(y+k-1).
\]

For a point on the bottom side \((x,-k)\)

\[
\text{value}=M_k-(k-x).
\]

---

### 1.  Locate the number 2026

\[
\sqrt{2026}=45.0\;\Rightarrow\;(2\cdot 22+1)^2 =45^{2}=2025<2026<(2\cdot23+1)^2=47^{2}=2209 .
\]

Hence \(2026\) lies on the next layer \(k=23\) and, being the first element of that layer, it is at  

\[
(23,-22).
\]

---

### 2.  The eight neighbours of \((23,-22)\)

| neighbour (x,y) | layer \(k\) | value |
|----------------|------------|-------|
| (22,-23) | 23 (bottom) | \(M_{23}-(23-22)=2209-1=2208\) |
| (23,-23) | 23 (bottom) | \(M_{23}=2209\) |
| (24,-23) | 24 (right‑side start) | \(S_{24}=(2\cdot24-1)^2+1=47^{2}+1=2210\) |
| (22,-22) | 22 (corner) | \(M_{22}=(2\cdot22+1)^2=45^{2}=2025\) |
| (24,-22) | 24 (right side) | \(S_{24}+1=2211\) |
| (22,-21) | 22 (right‑side start) | \(S_{22}=(2\cdot22-1)^2+1=43^{2}+1=1850\) |
| (23,-21) | 23 (right side) | \(S_{23}+1=2027\) |
| (24,-21) | 24 (right side) | \(S_{24}+2=2212\) |

---

### 3.  Sum

\[
\begin{aligned}
\Sigma &=2208+2209+2210+2025+2211+1850+2027+2212\\
      &=16952 .
\end{aligned}
\]

\[
\boxed{16952}
\]
